observationText: The NCI-H1373 cell line was included in a panel of 7 cancer cell lines called the NCI-7 Cell Line Panel, which was found to be suitable as a reference material for mass spectrometric analysis of the human proteome and may have applications as a universal standard proteomic reference.
The NCI-H1373 cell line was one of the cell lines included in the NCI-60 panel developed by the National Cancer Institute primarily for in vitro anticancer drug screening.
